313
00:11:00,980 --> 00:11:01,660
Now,

314
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:04,320
the fact

315
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:08,620
that it's constant everywhere is,

316
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:10,140
in other words,

317
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,640
mass times g doesn't vary from place to place,

318
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:13,420
that's this fact

319
00:11:13,420 --> 00:11:15,200
that gravity doesn't depend on where you are.

320
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,140
You can't tell where you

321
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:17,080
are in the flat space approximation.

322
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,770
But the fact that the force is

323
00:11:19,770 --> 00:11:21,620
proportional to the mass of an object,

324
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:23,460
that is not obvious.

325
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:24,720
In fact,

326
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,580
for most forces,

327
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:26,360
it's not true.

328
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,400
For electric forces,

329
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:32,000
the force is proportional to the electric charge,

330
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,260
not to the mass.

331
00:11:34,980 --> 00:11:37,920
And so gravitational forces are rather special.

332
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,980
The strength of the gravitational force on an object

333
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:42,460
is proportional to its mass.

334
00:11:43,819 --> 00:11:47,660
That characterizes gravity almost completely.

335
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,660
That's the special thing about gravity,

336
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:52,440
the force is proportional itself to the mass.

337
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:53,700
Well,

338
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:56,040
if we combine F equals mA

339
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,660
with the force law,

340
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,200
this is the law of force,

341
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,420
then what we find

342
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:04,820
is that mass times acceleration,

343
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:08,060
d second x,

344
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,920
now this is the vertical component,

345
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:12,100
by dt squared,

346
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:14,160
is equal to minus,

347
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:15,280
that's the minus,

348
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:16,940
mg,

349
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:18,980
period.

350
00:12:19,140 --> 00:12:19,640
That's it.

351
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:23,560
Now the interesting thing that happens in gravity

352
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:26,080
is that the mass cancels out from both sides.

353
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,300
That is what's special about gravity,

354
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:31,560
the mass cancels out from both sides.

355
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:36,360
And the consequence of that

356
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,340
is that the motion of an object,

357
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,160
its acceleration,

358
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,800
doesn't depend on the mass,

359
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:44,000
it doesn't depend on anything about the particle.

360
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,320
Particle,

361
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:46,660
object,

362
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:47,660
I'll use the word particle,

363
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,920
I don't necessarily mean a point,

364
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,060
a small particle,

365
00:12:52,260 --> 00:12:53,580
a baseball is a particle,

366
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:57,720
an eraser is a particle,

367
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,020
a piece of chalk is a particle,

368
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,820
that the motion of the object

369
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:05,380
doesn't depend on the mass of the object

370
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:06,220
or anything else.

371
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,740
The result of that

372
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,020
