00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:56,820
at the surface of the Earth,

431
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,220
at the surface of the Moon,

432
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:00,220
it's something smaller,

433
00:15:00,420 --> 00:15:01,400
on the surface of Jupiter,

434
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,440
it's something larger,

435
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:07,260
so it does depend on the mass of the planet,

436
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:10,060
but the acceleration doesn't depend

437
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:11,820
on the mass of the object you're dropping,

438
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,280
it depends on the mass of

439
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:14,640
the object you're dropping it onto,

440
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:17,560
but not the mass of the object that's dropping.

441
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:20,380
That fact,

442
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:22,520
that gravitational motion

443
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:24,680
is completely independent of mass,

444
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:25,680
is called,

445
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:27,060
or it's the simplest version

446
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:29,760
of something that's called the equivalence principle.

447
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,700
Why it's called the equivalence principle,

448
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:33,460
we'll come to later,

449
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:34,620
what's equivalent to what?

450
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:36,520
At this stage,

451
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:37,260
we could just say,

452
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:40,900
gravity is equivalent between all different objects,

453
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,140
independent of their mass,

454
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:44,660
but that is not exactly what the equivalence,

455
00:15:44,660 --> 00:15:46,380
an equivalence principle was about.

456
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:49,060
That has a consequence,

457
00:15:49,260 --> 00:15:50,440
an interesting consequence.

458
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,040
Supposing I take some object,

459
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:57,420
which is made up out of something

460
00:15:57,420 --> 00:16:00,600
which is very unrigid,

461
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:05,180
just a collection of point masses,

462
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:06,880
maybe,

463
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:10,600
let's even say they're not even exerting

464
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,840
any forces on each other.

465
00:16:11,980 --> 00:16:12,940
It's a cloud,

466
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:14,520
a very diffuse

467
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:21,740
cloud of particles,

468
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,500
and we watch it fall.

469
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:27,340
Let's suppose we start each particle from rest,

470
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:29,560
not all at the same height,

471
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,640
and we let them all fall.

472
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,760
Some particles are heavy,

473
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,060
some particles are light,

474
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:37,200
some of them may be big,

475
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:38,320
some of them may be small.

476
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,200
How does the whole thing fall?

477
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,300
The answer is,

478
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:45,300
all of the particles fall at exactly the same rate.

479
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:47,510
The consequence of it is

480
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:49,300
that the shape of this object

481
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,120
doesn't deform as it falls.

482
00:16:51,460 --> 00:16:53,720
It stays absolutely unchanged.

483
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:59,340
The relationship between the neighboring parts

484
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:00,500
are unchanged.

485
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:03,820
There are no stresses or strains

486
00:17:03,820 --> 00:17:06,300
which tend to deform the object.

487
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:09,359
So even if the object were held together

488
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:11,839
by some sort of struts or whatever,

489
00:17:12,099 --> 00:17:14,480
there would be no forces on those struts

490
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:16,660
because everything falls together.

491
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:20,020
The consequence of that

492
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:23,119
is that falling in a gravitational field

493
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:24,980
is undetectable.

494
00:17:25,220 --> 00:17:27,240
You can't tell that you're falling

495
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:29,900
in a gravitational field by...

496
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,380
When I say you can't tell,

497
00:17:31,580 --> 00:17:33,800
certainly you can tell the difference between

498
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:36,740
free fall and standing on the Earth.

499
00:17:37,940 --> 00:17:38,880
That's not the point.

500
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:40,690
The point is that you can't

501
00:17:40,690 --> 00:17:42,320
tell by looking at your neighbors

502
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:44,090
or anything else that there's

503
00:17:44,090 --> 00:17:45,860
a force being exerted on you

504
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:48,500
and that that force that's being exerted on you

505
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,940
is pulling you downward.

506
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:51,600
You might as well,

507
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,980
for all practical purposes,

508
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,600
be infinitely far from the Earth

509
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,540
with no gravity at all

510
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,560
and just sitting there

511
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:01,640
because as far as you can tell,

512
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:03,760
there's no tendency

513
00:18:03,820 --> 00:18:06,700
for the gravitational field to deform this object

514
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:07,560
or anything else.

515
00:18:07,780 --> 00:18:09,740
You cannot tell the difference

516
00:18:09,740 --> 00:18:12,100
between being in free space

517
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:14,720
infinitely far from anything with no forces

518
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:18,720
and falling freely in a gravitational field.

519
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:22,080
That's another statement of the equivalence principle.

520
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:24,280
Would you say not mechanically detectable?

521
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:25,460
Well,

522
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:25,880
in fact,

523
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:26,620
not detectable,

524
00:18:26,620 --> 00:18:26,920
period,

525
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,420
but so far not mechanically detectable.

526
00:18:30,980 --> 00:18:31,620
Well,

527
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:33,240
would it be optically detectable?

528
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:34,340
No.

529
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:35,980
No.

530
00:18:36,060 --> 00:18:36,680
For example,

531
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:39,120
these particles could be

532
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,260
equipped with lasers.

