00:21:26,477 --> 00:21:27,337
sure enough,

623
00:21:27,337 --> 00:21:28,697
my feet would feel funny,

624
00:21:28,797 --> 00:21:30,817
because they're used to having those forces

625
00:21:30,817 --> 00:21:32,057
exerted on their bottoms.

626
00:21:32,257 --> 00:21:33,017
You get it.

627
00:21:33,357 --> 00:21:33,977
I hope.

628
00:21:35,677 --> 00:21:38,057
So the fact that you feel funny in free fall

629
00:21:39,537 --> 00:21:41,577
is because you're not used to free fall.

630
00:21:42,237 --> 00:21:43,547
It doesn't matter whether you're

631
00:21:43,547 --> 00:21:44,857
infinitely far from the Earth,

632
00:21:44,857 --> 00:21:46,777
far from any gravitating object standing still,

633
00:21:46,997 --> 00:21:50,897
or freely falling in the presence of a gravitational field.

634
00:21:51,297 --> 00:21:51,817
Now,

635
00:21:51,817 --> 00:21:52,517
as I said,

636
00:21:52,517 --> 00:21:54,657
this will have to be modified in a little bit.

637
00:21:55,577 --> 00:21:57,677
There are such things as tidal forces.

638
00:21:58,597 --> 00:22:01,127
Those tidal forces are due to

639
00:22:01,127 --> 00:22:03,657
the fact that the Earth is curved,

