00:22:20,957 --> 00:22:22,737
where the Earth is infinitely big,

649
00:22:22,897 --> 00:22:23,697
pulling uniformly,

650
00:22:25,037 --> 00:22:29,357
there is no other effect of gravity

651
00:22:29,357 --> 00:22:31,657
that is any different than being in free space.

652
00:22:33,397 --> 00:22:33,997
Okay,

653
00:22:33,997 --> 00:22:34,217
again,

654
00:22:34,217 --> 00:22:36,177
that's known as the equivalent principle.

655
00:22:40,257 --> 00:22:40,857
Now,

656
00:22:40,857 --> 00:22:43,337
let's go on beyond the flat space

657
00:22:43,357 --> 00:22:45,757
or the flat Earth approximation

658
00:22:47,097 --> 00:22:48,997
and move on

659
00:22:51,577 --> 00:22:53,917
to Newton's theory of gravity.

660
00:22:55,577 --> 00:22:57,137
Newton's theory of gravity

661
00:22:59,317 --> 00:23:01,817
says every object in the universe

662
00:23:02,677 --> 00:23:04,527
exerts a gravitational force on

663
00:23:04,527 --> 00:23:06,377
every other object in the universe.

664
00:23:07,037 --> 00:23:08,717
Let's start with just two of them.

665
00:23:10,197 --> 00:23:11,437
Equal and opposite,

666
00:23:12,397 --> 00:23:12,997
attractive,

667
00:23:13,917 --> 00:23:15,637
attractive means that the direction

668
00:23:15,637 --> 00:23:17,357
of the force on one object

669
00:23:17,357 --> 00:23:19,337
is toward the other one.

670
00:23:21,637 --> 00:23:23,377
Equal and opposite forces,

671
00:23:23,437 --> 00:23:25,737
and the magnitude of the force,

672
00:23:26,437 --> 00:23:29,337
the magnitude of the force of one object on another,

673
00:23:29,577 --> 00:23:33,117
let's characterize them by a mass.

674
00:23:33,837 --> 00:23:35,877
Let's call this one little m.

675
00:23:36,877 --> 00:23:39,097
Think of it as a lighter mass,

676
00:23:39,177 --> 00:23:40,057
and this one,

677
00:23:40,057 --> 00:23:42,277
which we can imagine is a heavier object,

678
00:23:42,517 --> 00:23:43,797
we'll call it big M.

679
00:23:44,577 --> 00:23:45,377
All right,

680
00:23:45,377 --> 00:23:46,897
Newton's law of force

681
00:23:47,537 --> 00:23:48,777
is that the force

682
00:23:50,497 --> 00:23:53,757
is proportional to the product of the masses,

683
00:23:54,637 --> 00:23:56,857
making either mass heavier

684
00:23:56,857 --> 00:23:58,597
will increase the force.

685
00:23:59,837 --> 00:24:01,557
The product of the masses,

686
00:24:01,817 --> 00:24:03,597
big M times little m,

687
00:24:06,257 --> 00:24:08,117
inversely proportional to the square

688
00:24:08,117 --> 00:24:09,977
of the distance between them,

689
00:24:11,557 --> 00:24:13,177
let's call that r squared.

690
00:24:15,017 --> 00:24:17,237
Let's call the distance between them r,

691
00:24:19,757 --> 00:24:22,197
and there's a numerical constant.

692
00:24:22,517 --> 00:24:25,677
This law by itself could not possibly be right.

693
00:24:25,917 --> 00:24:27,897
It's not dimensionally consistent.

694
00:24:29,537 --> 00:24:32,617
If you work out the dimensions of force,

695
00:24:32,797 --> 00:24:33,417
mass,

696
00:24:33,417 --> 00:24:33,837
mass,

697
00:24:33,837 --> 00:24:34,377
and r,

698
00:24:34,637 --> 00:24:36,497
it's not dimensionally consistent.

699
00:24:36,697 --> 00:24:39,777
There has to be a numerical constant in there.

700
00:24:39,897 --> 00:24:39,957
So,

701
00:24:39,957 --> 00:24:42,717
and that numerical constant is called capital G,

702
00:24:44,597 --> 00:24:45,437
Newton's constant,

703
00:24:45,997 --> 00:24:47,177
and it's very small.

704
00:24:48,357 --> 00:24:49,877
It's a very small constant.

705
00:24:50,917 --> 00:24:52,257
I'll write down what it is.

706
00:24:52,377 --> 00:24:55,957
G is equal to six,

707
00:24:55,997 --> 00:24:58,437
or 6.7 roughly,

708
00:24:59,657 --> 00:25:02,177
times 10 to the minus 11th,

709
00:25:02,317 --> 00:25:03,677
which is a small number.

710
00:25:04,217 --> 00:25:05,337
So on the face of it,

711
00:25:05,377 --> 00:25:07,197
it seems that gravity is a very weak force.

712
00:25:09,497 --> 00:25:10,857
You might not think that

713
00:25:10,857 --> 00:25:12,217
gravity is such a weak force,

714
00:25:12,437 --> 00:25:15,657
but to convince yourself it's a weak force,

715
00:25:15,797 --> 00:25:17,877
there's a simple experiment that you can do,

