1455
00:50:39,777 --> 00:50:41,237
If it's small enough,

1456
00:50:41,997 --> 00:50:44,797
then the gradient of the gravitational field

1457
00:50:44,797 --> 00:50:47,157
across the size of the object

1458
00:50:47,157 --> 00:50:48,277
will be negligible,

1459
00:50:48,997 --> 00:50:51,317
and so all parts of it will experience

1460
00:50:51,317 --> 00:50:53,177
the same gravitational acceleration.

1461
00:50:53,937 --> 00:50:54,657
All right,

1462
00:50:54,657 --> 00:50:55,877
so tidal forces,

1463
00:50:55,897 --> 00:50:56,737
these are tidal forces,

1464
00:50:56,957 --> 00:50:59,417
these forces which tend to tear things apart vertically

1465
00:50:59,417 --> 00:51:00,497
and squish them this way,

1466
00:51:00,497 --> 00:51:01,277
tidal forces.

1467
00:51:01,917 --> 00:51:07,217
Tidal forces are forces which are real,

1468
00:51:07,217 --> 00:51:07,857
you feel them.

1469
00:51:09,217 --> 00:51:12,297
Do you recall if Newton calculated lunar tides?

1470
