1473
00:51:15,377 --> 00:51:15,577
yeah.

1474
00:51:17,077 --> 00:51:19,097
I don't know to what extent he calculated,

1475
00:51:19,417 --> 00:51:21,157
what do you mean calculated the...

1476
00:51:21,157 --> 00:51:22,667
As in this kind of a

1477
00:51:22,667 --> 00:51:24,177
system with the moon and the sun.

1478
00:51:24,417 --> 00:51:24,677
Well,

1479
00:51:24,677 --> 00:51:25,857
I doubt that he was capable,

1480
00:51:25,917 --> 00:51:27,897
I'm not sure whether he estimated the height

1481
00:51:27,897 --> 00:51:32,277
of the deformation of the oceans or not,

1482
00:51:32,777 --> 00:51:35,397
but I think he did understand this much about tides.

1483
00:51:36,477 --> 00:51:36,917
Okay,

1484
00:51:36,917 --> 00:51:39,817
so that's what's called tidal force,

1485
00:51:40,117 --> 00:51:41,757
and remember the tidal force

1486
00:51:42,837 --> 00:51:44,377
has this effect of stretching,

1487
00:51:46,977 --> 00:51:50,357
and in particular,

1488
00:51:51,597 --> 00:51:52,737
if we take the Earth,

1489
00:51:52,917 --> 00:51:55,317
just to tell you why it's called tidal forces,

1490
00:51:55,397 --> 00:51:57,077
of course it's because it has to do with tides,

1491
00:51:57,097 --> 00:51:58,197
I'm sure you all know the story,

1492
00:51:58,477 --> 00:52:00,317
but if this is the moon down here,

1493
00:52:01,757 --> 00:52:04,197
then the moon exerting forces on the Earth

1494
00:52:04,197 --> 00:52:05,897
exerts tidal forces on the Earth,

1495
00:52:06,077 --> 00:52:07,627
which means to some extent it

1496
00:52:07,627 --> 00:52:09,177
tends to stretch it this way

1497
00:52:09,177 --> 00:52:10,477
and squash it this way.

1498
