00:53:58,137 --> 00:53:58,657
Alright?

1547
00:54:00,397 --> 00:54:02,117
That's what this minus sign says.

1548
00:54:04,237 --> 00:54:04,717
Well,

1549
00:54:04,717 --> 00:54:07,657
you kind of retracted the minus sign at the front

1550
00:54:07,657 --> 00:54:10,057
and reversed the J-I.

1551
00:54:10,317 --> 00:54:10,657
Yeah.

1552
00:54:11,637 --> 00:54:12,557
So it's the direction.

1553
00:54:12,557 --> 00:54:14,247
We can get rid of the minus sign

1554
00:54:14,247 --> 00:54:15,937
at the front there by making this I-J.

1555
00:54:19,177 --> 00:54:22,097
R-I-J and R-J-I are opposite to each other.

1556
00:54:22,277 --> 00:54:25,477
One of them is the vector between I and J,

1557
00:54:26,297 --> 00:54:27,217
I and J,

1558
00:54:27,217 --> 00:54:28,367
and the other one is

1559
00:54:28,367 --> 00:54:29,517
the vector from J to I,

1560
00:54:29,777 --> 00:54:31,737
so they're equal and opposite to each other.

1561
00:54:33,177 --> 00:54:34,617
The minus sign there,

1562
00:54:34,857 --> 00:54:35,397
look,

1563
00:54:35,397 --> 00:54:37,717
as far as the minus sign goes,

1564
00:54:37,917 --> 00:54:41,277
all it means is that every one of

1565
00:54:41,277 --> 00:54:44,637
these particles is pulling on this particle toward it,

1566
00:54:45,337 --> 00:54:47,297
as opposed to pushing away from it.

1567
00:54:47,417 --> 00:54:49,627
It's just a convention which keeps

1568
00:54:49,627 --> 00:54:51,837
track of attraction instead of repulsion.

1569
00:54:53,017 --> 00:54:53,537
Yeah,

1570
00:54:53,537 --> 00:54:55,817
for the ice mass,

1571
00:54:55,817 --> 00:54:56,877
if that's the right word,

1572
00:54:56,877 --> 00:54:57,757
that makes sense,

1573
00:54:57,757 --> 00:54:59,087
but if you look at it

1574
00:54:59,087 --> 00:55:00,417
as a kind of an ensemble,

1575
00:55:00,597 --> 00:55:02,897
wouldn't there be a nonlinear component to it?

1576
00:55:02,997 --> 00:55:05,917
Because the I-th guy affects the J-th guy,

1577
00:55:06,097 --> 00:55:07,537
and then when you compute the J-th guy,

1578
00:55:07,537 --> 00:55:08,897
you know what I mean?

1579
00:55:09,177 --> 00:55:10,537
When you take into account the motion.

1580
00:55:10,957 --> 00:55:13,617
Now what this formula is for is supposing

1581
00:55:13,617 --> 00:55:16,277
you know the positions of all the others.

1582
00:55:17,577 --> 00:55:18,537
You know that.

1583
00:55:19,237 --> 00:55:22,377
Then what is the force on one additional one?

1584
00:55:22,677 --> 00:55:23,897
But you're perfectly right.

1585
00:55:24,217 --> 00:55:26,057
Once you let the system evolve,

1586
00:55:26,877 --> 00:55:29,777
then each one will cause a

1587
00:55:29,777 --> 00:55:32,677
change in motion in the other one,

1588
00:55:32,777 --> 00:55:33,937
and so it becomes a complicated,

1589
00:55:33,937 --> 00:55:34,597
as you say,

1590
00:55:34,597 --> 00:55:35,377
nonlinear mess.

1591
00:55:36,817 --> 00:55:40,237
But this formula is a formula for if

1592
00:55:40,237 --> 00:55:43,657
you knew the position and location of every particle,

1593
00:55:43,797 --> 00:55:44,857
this would be the force.

1594
00:55:45,537 --> 00:55:46,097
Okay?

1595
00:55:46,717 --> 00:55:48,537
Something you need to solve some

1596
00:55:48,537 --> 00:55:50,357
equations to know how the particles move.

1597
00:55:51,917 --> 00:55:54,237
But if you know where they are,

1598
00:55:54,237 --> 00:55:56,617
then this is the force on the I-th particle.

1599
00:55:58,357 --> 00:55:58,917
Alright,

1600
00:55:58,917 --> 00:56:01,297
let's come to the idea of the gravitational field.

1601
00:56:02,737 --> 00:56:04,507
The gravitational field is in some

1602
00:56:04,507 --> 00:56:06,277
ways similar to the electric field,

1603
00:56:06,357 --> 00:56:08,697
of an electric charge.

1604
00:56:11,557 --> 00:56:16,077
It's the combined effect of all the masses...

1605
00:56:22,557 --> 00:56:23,117
...everywhere's.

1606
00:56:24,477 --> 00:56:26,917
And the way you define it is as follows.

1607
00:56:27,497 --> 00:56:30,637
You imagine one more particle.

1608
00:56:30,897 --> 00:56:32,257
One more particle.

1609
00:56:32,357 --> 00:56:34,567
You can take it to be a very light

1610
00:56:34,567 --> 00:56:36,777
particle so it doesn't influence the motion of the others.

1611
00:56:37,737 --> 00:56:41,777
Add one more particle in your imagination.

1612
00:56:42,077 --> 00:56:44,097
You don't really have to add it in your imagination.

1613
00:56:44,357 --> 00:56:46,217
And ask what the force on it is.

1614
00:56:46,497 --> 00:56:49,047
The force is the sum of

1615
00:56:49,047 --> 00:56:51,597
the force due to all the others.

1616
00:56:52,017 --> 00:56:53,257
It is proportional.

1617
00:56:53,257 --> 00:56:55,477
Each term is proportional to

1618
00:56:55,477 --> 00:56:57,697
the mass of this extra particle.

1619
00:56:58,417 --> 00:56:59,697
This extra particle,

1620
00:56:59,697 --> 00:57:01,637
which may be imaginary,

1621
00:57:01,637 --> 00:57:03,257
is called a test particle.

1622
00:57:03,917 --> 00:57:05,787
It's a thing that you're imagining

1623
00:57:05,787 --> 00:57:07,657
testing out the gravitational field with.

1624
00:57:08,097 --> 00:57:10,127
You take a light little particle and you

1625
00:57:10,127 --> 00:57:12,157
put it here and you see how it accelerates.

1626
00:57:13,017 --> 00:57:15,047
Knowing how it accelerates tells you

1627
00:57:15,047 --> 00:57:17,077
how much force is on it.

1628
00:57:17,777 --> 00:57:18,257
Alright?

1629
00:57:19,337 --> 00:57:19,877
In fact,

1630
00:57:19,877 --> 00:57:21,297
it just tells you how it accelerates.

1631
00:57:21,437 --> 00:57:23,237
And you can go around and imagine things like this.

1632
00:57:23,237 --> 00:57:26,347
You're putting it in different places and mapping

1633
00:57:26,347 --> 00:57:29,457
out the force field that's on that particle.

1634
00:57:29,697 --> 00:57:31,517
Or the acceleration field.

1635
00:57:31,917 --> 00:57:34,757
Since we already know that the

1636
00:57:34,757 --> 00:57:37,597
force is proportional to the mass,

1637
00:57:39,197 --> 00:57:41,617
then we can just concentrate on the acceleration.

1638
00:57:42,297 --> 00:57:43,337
The acceleration,

1639
00:57:43,337 --> 00:57:45,267
all particles will have the

1640
00:57:45,267 --> 00:57:47,197
same acceleration independent of their mass.

1641
00:57:47,617 --> 00:57:48,987
So we don't even have to know

1642
00:57:48,987 --> 00:57:50,357
what the mass of the particle is.

1643
00:57:50,437 --> 00:57:51,457
We put something over there,

1644
00:57:51,457 --> 00:57:52,337
a little bit of dust,

1645
00:57:52,337 --> 00:57:54,357
and we see how it accelerates.

1646
00:57:54,837 --> 00:57:56,137
Acceleration is a vector.

1647
00:57:56,897 --> 00:58:00,497
And so we map out in space the

1648
00:58:00,497 --> 00:58:04,097
acceleration of a particle at every point in space.

1649
00:58:04,677 --> 00:58:06,957
Either imaginary or real particle.

1650
00:58:07,537 --> 00:58:09,677
And that gives us a vector

1651
00:58:09,677 --> 00:58:11,817
field at every point in space.

1652
00:58:12,297 --> 00:58:15,047
Every point in space there

1653
00:58:15,047 --> 00:58:17,797
is a gravitational field of acceleration.

1654
00:58:18,957 --> 00:58:20,857
It can be thought of as the acceleration.

1655
00:58:21,197 --> 00:58:22,317
You don't have to think of it as force.

1656
00:58:22,337 --> 00:58:23,217
Acceleration.

1657
00:58:23,637 --> 00:58:27,837
The acceleration of a point mass located at that position.

1658
00:58:28,097 --> 00:58:29,117
It's a vector.

1659
00:58:29,217 --> 00:58:30,557
It has a direction.

1660
00:58:30,977 --> 00:58:32,517
It has a magnitude.

1661
00:58:34,017 --> 00:58:36,197
And it's a function of position.

1662
00:58:37,197 --> 00:58:39,937
So we just give it a name.

1663
00:58:41,097 --> 00:58:45,417
The acceleration due to all the gravitating objects.

1664
00:58:46,457 --> 00:58:47,637
It's a vector.

1665
00:58:48,477 --> 00:58:50,877
And it depends on position.

1666
00:58:51,457 --> 00:58:51,977
Here,

1667
00:58:51,977 --> 00:58:53,657
x means location.

1668
00:58:53,917 --> 00:58:56,557
It means all of the components of position.

1669
00:58:56,797 --> 00:58:56,977
x,

1670
00:58:56,977 --> 00:58:57,237
y,

1671
00:58:57,237 --> 00:58:57,577
and z.

1672
00:58:58,217 --> 00:58:59,947
And it depends on all

1673
00:58:59,947 --> 00:59:01,677
the other masses in the problem.

1674
00:59:06,357 --> 00:59:08,457
That is what's called a gravitational field.

1675
00:59:10,737 --> 00:59:12,677
It's very similar to the electric field,

1676
00:59:12,857 --> 00:59:16,997
except the electric field is force per unit charge.

1677
00:59:17,837 --> 00:59:19,347
It's the force on an object

1678
00:59:19,347 --> 00:59:20,857
divided by the charge of the object.

1679
00:59:20,877 --> 00:59:23,697
The gravitational field is the force on the

1680
00:59:23,697 --> 00:59:26,517
object divided by the mass on the object.

1681
00:59:26,757 --> 00:59:29,137
Since the force is proportional to the mass,

1682
00:59:29,417 --> 00:59:32,587
the acceleration field doesn't depend on

1683
00:59:32,587 --> 00:59:35,757
which kind of particle we're talking about.

1684
00:59:37,057 --> 00:59:40,657
So that's the idea of a gravitational field.

1685
00:59:40,977 --> 00:59:42,057
It's a vector field.

1686
00:59:42,637 --> 00:59:44,617
And it varies from place to place.

1687
00:59:44,897 --> 00:59:46,657
And of course if the particles are moving,

1688
00:59:46,897 --> 00:59:48,517
it also varies in time.

1689
00:59:49,037 --> 00:59:50,517
If everything is in motion,

1690
00:59:50,877 --> 00:59:53,397
the gravitational field will also depend on time.

1691
00:59:56,277 --> 00:59:58,157
We can even work out what it is.

1692
00:59:58,457 --> 01:00:01,017
We know what the force on the i-th particle is.

1693
01:00:02,717 --> 01:00:04,587
The force on a particle

1694
01:00:04,587 --> 01:00:06,457
is the mass times the acceleration.

1695
01:00:07,077 --> 01:00:09,077
So if we want to find the acceleration,

1696
01:00:09,377 --> 01:00:12,017
let's take the i-th particle to be the test particle.

1697
01:00:12,397 --> 01:00:16,497
The little i represents the test particle over here.

1698
01:00:16,937 --> 01:00:20,157
Let's erase the intermediate step over here.

1699
01:00:20,877 --> 01:00:27,037
And write that this is m i times a i,

1700
01:00:27,277 --> 01:00:29,257
but let me call it now capital A.

1701
01:00:30,457 --> 01:00:34,017
The acceleration of a particle at position x

1702
01:00:35,497 --> 01:00:37,857
is given by the right-hand side.

1703
01:00:38,297 --> 01:00:41,037
And we can cross out the m i,

1704
01:00:41,197 --> 01:00:42,937
because it cancels from both sides.

1705
01:00:44,477 --> 01:00:45,977
So here's a formula

1706
01:00:47,457 --> 01:00:50,857
for the gravitational field,

1707
01:00:50,857 --> 01:00:52,537
at an arbitrary point,

1708
01:00:52,717 --> 01:00:57,557
due to a whole bunch of massive objects.

1709
01:00:57,877 --> 01:00:59,897
A whole bunch of massive objects,

1710
01:01:02,237 --> 01:01:05,277
an arbitrary particle put over here,

