01:14:19,037 --> 01:14:20,517
You could have a velocity vector

2082
01:14:20,517 --> 01:14:22,637
having a divergence

2083
01:14:24,057 --> 01:14:26,537
because the water is...

2084
01:14:26,537 --> 01:14:27,957
Not because water is flowing in,

2085
01:14:28,057 --> 01:14:29,457
but because it's thinning out.

2086
01:14:29,917 --> 01:14:30,577
Yeah,

2087
01:14:30,577 --> 01:14:31,817
that's also possible.

2088
01:14:32,237 --> 01:14:32,837
Okay,

2089
01:14:32,837 --> 01:14:33,717
but let's keep it simple.

2090
01:14:34,977 --> 01:14:35,737
All right,

2091
01:14:35,737 --> 01:14:36,637
and you can have...

2092
01:14:36,637 --> 01:14:38,637
The idea of a divergence makes sense

2093
01:14:38,637 --> 01:14:40,777
in three dimensions just as well as two dimensions.

2094
01:14:41,117 --> 01:14:42,957
You simply have to imagine

2095
01:14:42,957 --> 01:14:45,657
that all of space is filled with water,

2096
01:14:45,757 --> 01:14:48,577
and there are some hidden pipes coming in,

2097
01:14:48,617 --> 01:14:50,697
depositing water in different places

2098
01:14:51,377 --> 01:14:53,917
so that it's spreading out away from points

2099
01:14:53,917 --> 01:14:55,977
in three-dimensional space.

2100
01:14:56,417 --> 01:14:58,037
In three-dimensional space,

2101
01:14:58,337 --> 01:14:59,837
this is the expression

2102
01:14:59,917 --> 01:15:00,957
for the divergence.

2103
01:15:01,777 --> 01:15:04,677
If this were the velocity vector at every point,

2104
01:15:04,957 --> 01:15:06,877
