2105
01:15:06,997 --> 01:15:08,657
and that would tell you how much new water

2106
01:15:08,657 --> 01:15:10,397
is coming in at each point of space.

2107
01:15:10,837 --> 01:15:11,957
So that's the divergence.

2108
01:15:12,657 --> 01:15:13,217
Now,

2109
01:15:13,217 --> 01:15:14,437
there's a theorem which...

2110
01:15:15,157 --> 01:15:16,857
The hint of the theorem

2111
01:15:16,857 --> 01:15:18,877
was just given by Michael there.

2112
01:15:19,617 --> 01:15:21,097
It's called Gauss's theorem,

2113
01:15:22,297 --> 01:15:25,317
and it says something intuitive,

2114
01:15:26,197 --> 01:15:27,837
very intuitively obvious.

2115
01:15:29,917 --> 01:15:31,237
You take a surface,

2116
01:15:31,237 --> 01:15:32,017
any surface,

2117
01:15:33,957 --> 01:15:35,257
take any surface

2118
01:15:39,137 --> 01:15:41,457
or any curve in two dimensions,

2119
01:15:43,017 --> 01:15:45,317
and now suppose there's a vector field.

2120
01:15:46,697 --> 01:15:47,697
Vector field,

2121
01:15:47,697 --> 01:15:48,177
points.

2122
01:15:52,017 --> 01:15:54,557
Think of it as the flow of water.

2123
01:15:56,557 --> 01:15:59,117
And now let's take the total amount

2124
01:15:59,117 --> 01:16:01,857
of water that's flowing out of the surface.

2125
01:16:03,157 --> 01:16:03,717
Obviously,

2126
01:16:03,717 --> 01:16:04,377
there's some water

2127
01:16:04,377 --> 01:16:05,497
flowing out over here,

2128
01:16:06,177 --> 01:16:07,057
and of course,

2129
01:16:07,057 --> 01:16:07,797
we want to subtract

2130
01:16:07,797 --> 01:16:09,477
the water that's flowing in.

2131
01:16:10,397 --> 01:16:12,237
Let's calculate the total amount

2132
01:16:12,237 --> 01:16:14,197
of water that's flowing out of the surface.

2133
01:16:14,897 --> 01:16:17,237
That's an integral over the surface.

2134
01:16:17,677 --> 01:16:18,777
Why is it an integral?

2135
01:16:19,017 --> 01:16:20,417
Because we have to add up

2136
01:16:20,417 --> 01:16:22,677
the flows of water outward.

2137
01:16:23,497 --> 01:16:25,117
Where the water is coming inward,

2138
01:16:25,257 --> 01:16:28,137
that's just negative flow.

2139
01:16:28,137 --> 01:16:29,957
Negative outward flow.

2140
01:16:30,237 --> 01:16:32,397
We add up the total outward flow

2141
01:16:32,397 --> 01:16:34,557
by breaking up the surface

2142
01:16:34,557 --> 01:16:36,857
into little pieces and asking

2143
01:16:36,857 --> 01:16:38,797
how much flow is coming out

2144
01:16:38,797 --> 01:16:40,077
from each little piece here.

2145
01:16:40,137 --> 01:16:41,917
How much water is passing out

2146
01:16:41,917 --> 01:16:43,037
through the surface.

2147
01:16:44,837 --> 01:16:47,137
If the water is incompressible,

2148
01:16:48,977 --> 01:16:51,197
incompressible means its density is fixed,

2149
01:16:51,357 --> 01:16:52,397
and furthermore,

2150
01:16:52,397 --> 01:16:54,097
the depth of the water

2151
01:16:54,097 --> 01:16:55,097
is being kept fixed.

2152
01:16:55,157 --> 01:16:57,057
There's only one way that water

2153
01:16:57,057 --> 01:16:58,877
can come out of the surface,

2154
01:16:59,017 --> 01:17:00,457
and that's if it's being pumped in,

2155
01:17:00,497 --> 01:17:01,297
if there's a divergence.

2156
01:17:03,317 --> 01:17:05,157
The divergence could be over here,

2157
01:17:05,297 --> 01:17:05,997
it could be over here,

2158
01:17:06,097 --> 01:17:06,797
it could be over here,

2159
01:17:06,877 --> 01:17:07,577
it could be over here.

2160
01:17:07,937 --> 01:17:08,717
In fact,

2161
01:17:08,717 --> 01:17:10,297
anywhere where there's a divergence

2162
01:17:10,977 --> 01:17:14,077
will cause an effect in which water

2163
01:17:14,077 --> 01:17:15,537
will flow out of this region here.

2164
01:17:15,797 --> 01:17:16,897
So there's a connection.

2165
01:17:17,377 --> 01:17:18,697
There's a connection between

2166
01:17:18,697 --> 01:17:20,637
what's going on on the boundary

2167
01:17:20,637 --> 01:17:21,437
of this region,

2168
01:17:21,617 --> 01:17:24,097
how much water is flowing through the boundary

2169
01:17:24,097 --> 01:17:24,957
on the one hand,

2170
01:17:25,057 --> 01:17:26,837
and what the divergence is

2171
01:17:27,057 --> 01:17:27,657
in the interior.

2172
01:17:29,817 --> 01:17:31,377
There's a connection between the two,

2173
01:17:31,477 --> 01:17:32,717
and that connection is called

2174
01:17:32,717 --> 01:17:33,717
Gauss's theorem.

2175
01:17:34,297 --> 01:17:36,837
What it says is that the integral

2176
01:17:36,837 --> 01:17:38,797
of the divergence in the interior,

2177
01:17:39,097 --> 01:17:40,677
that's the total amount of flow

2178
01:17:40,677 --> 01:17:43,337
coming in from outside,

2179
01:17:43,517 --> 01:17:45,137
from underneath the bottom of the lake,

2180
01:17:45,847 --> 01:17:47,317
the total integrated,

2181
01:17:49,137 --> 01:17:50,837
and now by integrated I mean

2182
01:17:50,837 --> 01:17:51,817
in the sense of an integral,

2183
01:17:52,077 --> 01:17:55,997
the integrated amount of flow in,

2184
01:17:55,997 --> 01:17:57,857
that's the integral of the divergence,

2185
01:18:00,717 --> 01:18:03,437
the integral over the interior,

2186
01:18:04,217 --> 01:18:06,117
in the three-dimensional case,

2187
01:18:06,317 --> 01:18:08,197
it would be integral dxdy dz,

2188
01:18:09,097 --> 01:18:11,237
over the interior of this region

2189
01:18:11,817 --> 01:18:15,377
of the divergence of A,

2190
01:18:16,897 --> 01:18:18,577
if you like to think of A

2191
01:18:18,577 --> 01:18:19,777
as the velocity field,

2192
01:18:19,777 --> 01:18:20,337
that's fine,

2193
01:18:20,557 --> 01:18:23,977
is equal to the total amount of flow

2194
01:18:23,977 --> 01:18:25,977
that's going out through the interior

2195
01:18:25,997 --> 01:18:26,497
through the boundary.

2196
01:18:27,297 --> 01:18:28,577
And how do we write that?

2197
01:18:29,697 --> 01:18:31,657
The total amount of flow that's flowing

2198
01:18:31,657 --> 01:18:33,057
outward through the boundary,

2199
01:18:33,297 --> 01:18:34,457
we break up,

2200
01:18:34,557 --> 01:18:35,977
let's take the three-dimensional case,

2201
01:18:36,177 --> 01:18:38,217
we break up the boundary into little cells.

2202
01:18:39,137 --> 01:18:41,097
Each little cell is a little area.

2203
01:18:41,877 --> 01:18:44,137
Let's call each one of those little areas

2204
01:18:46,557 --> 01:18:47,597
d sigma.

2205
01:18:48,997 --> 01:18:50,037
d sigma,

2206
01:18:50,037 --> 01:18:51,897
sigma stands for surface area,

2207
01:18:52,157 --> 01:18:53,737
sigma is the Greek letter sigma,

2208
01:18:53,857 --> 01:18:54,937
it stands for surface area.

2209
01:18:55,997 --> 01:18:57,557
This three-dimensional integral

2210
01:18:59,997 --> 01:19:02,337
over the interior here

2211
01:19:02,797 --> 01:19:05,537
is equal to a two-dimensional integral

2212
01:19:05,537 --> 01:19:07,897
d sigma over the surface,

2213
01:19:08,837 --> 01:19:11,657
and it is just the component

2214
01:19:11,657 --> 01:19:17,077
of A perpendicular to the surface.

2215
01:19:18,757 --> 01:19:22,617
Let's call it A perpendicular to the surface d sigma.

2216
01:19:23,077 --> 01:19:25,597
A perpendicular to the surface

2217
01:19:25,997 --> 01:19:28,317
is the amount of flow that's coming out

2218
01:19:28,317 --> 01:19:29,637
of each one of these little boxes.

2219
01:19:30,577 --> 01:19:31,217
Notice,

2220
01:19:31,217 --> 01:19:31,857
incidentally,

2221
01:19:31,857 --> 01:19:33,997
that if there's a flow along the surface,

2222
01:19:34,317 --> 01:19:37,077
it doesn't give rise to any fluid coming out.

2223
01:19:37,537 --> 01:19:40,257
It's only the flow perpendicular to the surface,

2224
01:19:40,397 --> 01:19:42,957
the component of the flow perpendicular to the surface,

2225
01:19:43,157 --> 01:19:45,857
which carries fluid from the inside to the outside.

2226
01:19:46,477 --> 01:19:50,077
So we integrate the perpendicular component

2227
01:19:51,077 --> 01:19:52,497
of the flow

2228
01:19:54,837 --> 01:19:56,677
over the surface,

2229
01:19:56,917 --> 01:19:58,037
that's the little d sigma here,

2230
01:19:58,337 --> 01:20:00,517
that gives us the total amount of fluid

2231
01:20:00,517 --> 01:20:01,897
coming out per unit time,

2232
01:20:01,897 --> 01:20:02,597
for example,

2233
01:20:03,657 --> 01:20:05,277
and that has to be equal

2234
01:20:05,277 --> 01:20:08,097
to the amount of fluid that's being generated

2235
01:20:08,097 --> 01:20:09,997
in the interior by the divergence.

2236
01:20:10,697 --> 01:20:12,297
This is Gauss's theorem,

2237
01:20:12,537 --> 01:20:14,237
the relationship between

2238
01:20:14,237 --> 01:20:16,437
the integral of the divergence

2239
01:20:16,437 --> 01:20:18,277
on the interior of some region

2240
01:20:18,277 --> 01:20:20,877
and the integral over the boundary

2241
01:20:24,417 --> 01:20:26,917
where it's measuring the flux,

2242
01:20:27,297 --> 01:20:29,237
the amount of stuff that's coming out

2243
01:20:29,237 --> 01:20:30,057
through the boundary.

2244
01:20:32,117 --> 01:20:33,037
Fundamental theorem.

2245
01:20:38,697 --> 01:20:40,437
Let's see what it says now.

2246
01:20:42,517 --> 01:20:44,977
Any questions about Gauss's theorem here?

2247
01:20:46,817 --> 01:20:47,997
You'll see how it works.

2248
01:20:48,017 --> 01:20:48,957
I'll show you how it works in a minute.

2249
01:20:50,877 --> 01:20:53,397
You mentioned that for water,

2250
01:20:53,437 --> 01:20:54,817
as in compressible,

2251
01:20:54,997 --> 01:20:57,157
does that mean that we're,

2252
01:20:57,297 --> 01:21:00,797
that we were dealing with a compressible fluid?

2253
01:21:01,137 --> 01:21:01,557
Well,

2254
01:21:01,557 --> 01:21:02,117
yeah,

2255
01:21:02,117 --> 01:21:02,777
you could have,

2256
01:21:02,897 --> 01:21:03,297
sure,

2257
01:21:03,297 --> 01:21:04,977
if you had a compressible fluid,

2258
01:21:05,117 --> 01:21:07,017
you could discover that all the fluid

2259
01:21:07,017 --> 01:21:09,317
out in the boundary here is all moving inwards

2260
01:21:09,657 --> 01:21:10,697
in every direction

2261
01:21:10,697 --> 01:21:13,117
without any new fluid being formed.

2262
01:21:13,877 --> 01:21:14,657
In fact,

2263
01:21:14,657 --> 01:21:15,497
what's happening is just

2264
01:21:15,497 --> 01:21:16,457
the fluid is getting squeezed.

2265
01:21:16,777 --> 01:21:18,417
But if the fluid can't squeeze,

2266
01:21:18,557 --> 01:21:19,977
if you cannot compress it,

2267
01:21:20,877 --> 01:21:23,917
the only way that fluid could be flowing in

2268
01:21:23,917 --> 01:21:26,137
is if it's being removed somehow from the center,

2269
01:21:26,777 --> 01:21:30,817
if it's being removed by invisible pipes

2270
01:21:30,817 --> 01:21:32,037
that are carrying it off.

2271
01:21:34,817 --> 01:21:37,137
